{{Orphan|date=February 2013}}
In [[category theory]], a branch of [[mathematics]], a '''pulation square''' (also called a '''Doolittle diagram''') is a diagram that is simultaneously a [[Pullback (category theory)|pullback]] square and a [[pushout (category theory)|pushout]] square. It is a [[Dual (category theory)|self-dual]] concept.
